label.value: normal microtubule cytoskeleton organization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule cytoskeleton organization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Microtubule cytoskeleton organization is the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising microtubules and their associated proteins.

label.value: abnormal linear element assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which linear element assembly is abnormal. Linear element assembly includes the assembly of LinE complexes and their close association with chromatin to form a proteinaceous scaffold (related to the synaptonemal complex) on chromosomes during meiotic prophase.

label.value: abnormal microtubule dynamics during vegetative growth

value.value: A  microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule growth (polymerization), catastrophe (the transition from growth to shrinkage), shrinkage (depolymerization), or rescue (the transition from shrinkage to growth) is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal microtubule depolymerization during vegetative growth

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule depolymerization, i.e. the removal of tubulin dimers from a microtubule, is abnormal.

label.value: decreased rate of microtubule depolymerization during vegetative growth

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule depolymerization, i.e. the removal of tubulin dimers from a microtubule, occurs at a lower rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: decreased microtubule polymerization or depolymerization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule polymerization or depolymerization, by the addition or removal of tubulin dimers respectively, occurs to a lesser extent than normal. Microtubules are thus less dynamic than normal.

label.value: abnormal protein ubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal mitochondrion inheritance during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrion inheritance is abnormal. Mitochondrion inheritance is a cellular process that results in the distribution of mitochondria into daughter cells after mitosis or meiosis, mediated by interactions between mitochondria and the cytoskeleton.

label.value: abolished mitochondrion inheritance during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrion inheritance is abolished, resulting in the formation of a daughter cell that lacks mitochondria.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to linear element

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to linear elements is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at linear elements and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased nuclear RNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in the cell nucleus is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein ubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal sporulation resulting in formation of ascus containing non-uniform spores

value.value: A sporulation phenotype that results in the formation of an ascus that contains spores of non-uniform size and DNA content.

label.value: normal glutamate-ammonia ligase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutamate-ammonia ligase (also known as glutamine synthetase) activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal pyruvate dehydrogenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyruvate dehydrogenase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased pyruvate dehydrogenase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of pyruvate dehydrogenase activity is decreased.

label.value: abnormal citrate (Si)-synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of citrate (Si)-synthase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased citrate (Si)-synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of citrate (Si)-synthase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased citrate (Si)-synthase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of citrate (Si)-synthase activity is increased.

label.value: abnormal aconitate hydratase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of aconitate hydratase (also known as aconitase) activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased aconitate hydratase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of aconitate hydratase (also known as aconitase) activity is increased.

label.value: abnormal isocitrate dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of isocitrate dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased isocitrate dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of isocitrate dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity is increased.

label.value: resistance to anisomycin

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of anisomycin than normal.

label.value: unequal meiotic chromosome segregation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which chromosomes are not segregated equally to the two spindle poles in a meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: normal volume vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell has a normal volume.

label.value: abolished horsetail movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which horsetail movement does not occur. Horsetail movement is the oscillatory movement of the nucleus that takes place during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to cell cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the cell cortex and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cell cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule cytoskeleton is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with the microtubule cytoskeleton and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule cytoskeleton is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule cytoskeleton is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule cytoskeleton does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to cortical microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cortical microtubule cytoskeleton is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with the cortical microtubule cytoskeleton and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to cortical microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cortical microtubule cytoskeleton is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cortical microtubule cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cortical microtubule cytoskeleton is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to cortical microtubule cytoskeleton during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cortical microtubule cytoskeleton during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the spindle pole body and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal nucleus positioning in prospore

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which nucleus localization is abnormal in a prospore.

label.value: normal spore morphology

value.value: A cell phenotype characterized by normal spore morphology, i.e. the size, shape, and structure of the spore are indistinguishable from wild type.

label.value: inviable spore with normal morphology

value.value: A viability phenotype in which a spore is unable to survive under conditions in which wild type spores survive, and has a normal morphology (i.e. size, shape, or structure). An inviable spore does not germinate.

label.value: swollen spheroid vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is shaped in the form of a spheroid, and has a larger volume than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: normal volume spheroid vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is shaped in the form of a spheroid, and has a normal volume.

label.value: swollen spherical vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is shaped in the form of a sphere, and has a larger volume than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: normal volume spherical vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is shaped in the form of a sphere, and has a normal volume.

label.value: aseptate

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell does not contain a septum.

label.value: elongated aseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell does not contain a septum and is elongated.
